Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light orange-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 173, 7, with more of the text, accidentally trimmed off. Name Simos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0010.20.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0492)
